{"lemma":"جُزْآنِ","slug":"جُزْآنِ","root":"ج.ز.#","root_slug":"ج-ز-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ز-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جُزْء","root":"جزأ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5673","n5674"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D8%B2%D9%92%D8%A2%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"component, constituent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"division"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fraction"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"section, segment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"part, piece, portion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"juz’ (thirtieth part of the Qur'an, the prescribed amount to be read each day of the month of Ramadan)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/d͡ʒuzʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5673","headword_ar":"جَزْءٌ","root":"jzA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juzo'N","text_ar":"جُزْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  It is said by El-Khattábee to be a name for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTb","text_ar":"رُطب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTobN","text_ar":"رُطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh, pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1 and 4,)], with the people of El-Medeeneh; and occurs in a trad.; but the reading commonly known is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrw","text_ar":"جرو"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n5674","headword_ar":"جُزْءٌ","root":"jzA^","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"division,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of a thing; (Msb, TA;) properly and conventionally; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazo'N","text_ar":"جَزْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a constituent part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing, as of a ship, and of a house or tent, and of a sum in reckoning; (B, TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ingredient"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any compound or mixture;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajozaA='N","text_ar":"اَجْزَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K, &c. :) it has no other pl. (Sb, TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A volume"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a book.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a verse. (TA.) ―         -b4-  In the Kur [xliii. 14], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajaEaluwA lahu mino EibaAdihi juzo'FA","text_ar":"وَجَعَلُوا لَهُ مِنْ عِبَادِهِ جُزْءًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or, as some read,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juzu'FA","text_ar":"جُزُءًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd,) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Females;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;;) i. e., they asserted the angels to be the daughters of God: so says Th: and Aboo-Is-hák says that it means, they asserted God's share of offspring to be the females; but that he had not found this in old poetry, nor had persons worthy of confidence related it on the authority of the Arabs [of the classical times]: Z disallows it, asserting it to be a lie against the Arabs; and Bd follows him: El-Khafájee says that the word may be used figuratively; for, as Eve was created of a part ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juzo'","text_ar":"جُزْء"},{"kind":"text","text":") of Adam, the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jz'","text_ar":"جزء"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be applied to denote the female. (MF, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}